.TH GHOSTCTL 1 "April 2026" "ghostctl" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ghostctl \- Linux system, homelab, and virtualization management toolkit
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ghostctl
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fICOMMAND\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ghostctl
is a modular command-line toolkit for Linux administration workflows including system maintenance, Docker, networking, storage, Proxmox, VFIO, UEFI, security, and development environments.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -H, --headless
Run without interactive prompts.
.TP
.B -n, --non-interactive
Alias for --headless.
.TP
.B -D, --dry-run
Show what would be done without making changes.
.TP
.B -y, --yes
Automatically answer yes to prompts.
.TP
.B -p, --plain
Use plain output without colors or emoji.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show help.
.TP
.B -V, --version
Show version.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B completion <bash|zsh|fish>
Generate shell completions.
.TP
.B support paths
Show GhostCTL state, support, and log paths.
.TP
.B support doctor
Run quick support readiness checks for state paths, log paths, and visible external tools.
.TP
.B support logs
Show recent GhostCTL activity logs.
.TP
.B support bundle [--output PATH] [--redact-paths] [--gzip|--tarball] [--log-tail LINES]
Write a support diagnostics bundle plus JSON metadata sidecar. By default bundles are written under the XDG state directory, normally ~/.local/state/ghostctl/support.
.TP
.B support bundle --redact-paths
Redact home directory paths and common local identifiers before sharing bundle output.
.TP
.B support bundle --tarball
Write a tar.gz archive containing the text report and JSON metadata.
.TP
.B list
List available commands.
.TP
.B version
Show detailed version information.
.SH COMPLETIONS
.TP
.B ghostctl completion bash
Generate bash completion script.
.TP
.B ghostctl completion zsh
Generate zsh completion script.
.TP
.B ghostctl completion fish
Generate fish completion script.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/state/ghostctl/logs/history.log
Default activity history log on Linux systems with an XDG state directory.
.TP
.I ~/.local/state/ghostctl/support/
Default support bundle output directory.
.SH SEE ALSO
Run \fBghostctl --help\fR and \fBghostctl <command> --help\fR for the live command reference.
